text: Huba Rozsnyai (14 December 1942 - 4 December 2020) was a Hungarian sprinter. He competed in the men's 100 metres at the 1964 Summer Olympics. Rozsnyai died on 4 December 2020, just ten days before his 77. ==References== Category:1942 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Hungarian sprinters Category:Olympians for Hungary
